# Security Policy

## Supported Versions

This project is provided as an open-access educational solution.
The following components are supported:

| Component        | Support Level |
|------------------|---------------|
| Admin Server     | Supported     |
| Client Demo App  | Supported     |
| Production MSI   | On Request    |

Security updates and fixes are applied to the actively maintained versions.

## Reporting a Vulnerability

If you discover a security vulnerability, please report it responsibly.

**Contact:**
Popol Y. Elonda  
Email: Popolelonda@gmail.com or pelonda@byupathway.edu

Please include:
- A description of the issue
- Steps to reproduce (if applicable)
- Impact assessment (if known)

Do **not** publicly disclose vulnerabilities before they are reviewed.


## Security Principles

This project follows these principles:
- Least privilege access
- Secure password hashing
- No plaintext credential storage
- Controlled administrative access
- Local-first execution for client security

## Disclaimer

This software is provided for educational and public-interest use.
Institutions deploying this solution are responsible for their own security audits and operational compliance.
